@Entity - use to mark any class as Entity
@Table - use to change the table details
@Id - use to mark column as id(primary key)
@GeneratedValue - hibernate will automatically generate values for that 
using an internal sequence
@Column - can be used to specify column mappings. For ex , to change the col
name in the associcated table in database
@Transient - This tells hibernate not to save this field
@Temporal - @Temporal over a date field tell hibernate the format in which the date needs to be saved
@Lob - tells hibernate that this is a large object , not a simple object
@OneToOne  @OneToMany @ManyToOne @JoinColumn etc
